SERVLET API:-
IN SERVLET API WE HAVE BUILT IN CLASSES ALONG WITH THAT BUILT IN 
INTERFACES.
EXAMPLE:-
1.SERVLET INTERFACE
2.GENERIC SERVLET CLASS
3.HTTP SERVLET CLASS
4.REQUEST DISPATCHER
5.HTTP SERVLET REQUEST
6.HTTP SERVLET RESPONSE ETC.
->IT IS PRESENT IN JAVAX.SERVLET PACKAGE.
->SERVLET INTERFACE IS THE PARENT FOR ALL THE CLASSES AND INTERFACES
IN SERVLET API.
->IT WILL PRIVIDE FEW FUNCATIONALITY,WHICH EVERY SERVLET HAS TO INHERIT.

->SERVLET INTERFACE WILL HAVE 5 MAIN BUILT IN METHODS.
->IN WHICH 3 METHODS ARE LIFE CYCLE METHODS.

LIFE CYCLE:-
1.SERVLET CLASS WILL BE LOADED WITH THE HELP OF CLASSLODER
2.CREATING INSTANCE OF SERVLET CLASS
3.invoke init()method by web container
4.service method by web container
5.destroy()method by web container


1.GENERIC SERVLET:-IT IS A SERVLET CLASS WHICH IS PRESENT IN SERVLET API.
->IT IMPLEMENTS SERVLET INTERFACE.
->IT IS PROTOCOL INDEPENDENT.
->IT CAN HANDLE ANY TYPE OF REQUEST.
->IT WILL IMPLEMENT All the methods of servlet interface.
->LIKE init()method,service(),destroy()method and so on.
->we can create servlet with the help of generic servlet class also.

2.HTTP SERVLET:-IT IS A SERVLET CLASS WHICH IS PRESENT IN SERVLET API.
->IT IS A CHILD CLASS FOR SERVLET INTERFACE.
->IT IS PROTOCOL DEPENDENT.
->IT WILL HANDLE ALL HTTP REQUEST AND RESPONSE.
->IT WILL INHERIT ALL THE METHODS OF SERVLET INTERFACE.
->IT WILL HAVE doGet(),doPost(),doHead(),doTrace() methods.

3.REQUEST DISPATCHER:-IT IS A INTERFACE WHICH IS PRESENT IN SERVLET API.
->REQUEST DISPATCHER INTERFACE PROVIDES THE FACILITY TO DISPATCH THE
REQUEST TO ONE RESOURCE TO ANOTHER RESOURCE.
->IT MAY BE HTML,SERVLET OR JSP.

->IN THIS INTERFACE WE HAVE TWO METHODS:-
1.FORWARD() METHOD:-IT FORWARDS A REQUEST FROM SERVLET TO ANOTHER RESOURCE
(SERVLET,JSP OR HTML FILE).

2.INCLUDE() METHOD:-IT INCLUDES THE CONTENT OF RESOURCE IN THE RESPONSE.

4.SENDREDIRECT() METHOD:-IT IS A METHOD OF HTTP SERVLET RESPONSE INTERFACE
IT CAN BE USED TO REDIRECT RESPONSE TO ANOTHER RESOURCE,IT MAY BE
SERVLET OR JSP PAGE.

5.SERVLET CONFIG:-SERVLET CONFIG IS A INTERFACE WHICH IS PRESENT INSIDE
SERVLET API.
AN OBJECT OF SERVLET CONFIG IS CREATED BY WEB CONTAINER FOR EACH SERVLET.
THIS OBJECT IS USED TO GET CONFIGURATION INFORMATION FROM WEB.XML FILE.

6.SERVLET CONTEXT:-IT IS A INTERFACE ,WHICH IS PRESENT INSIDE
SERVLET API.
->AN OBJECT OF SERVLET CONTEXT IS USED TO GET CONFIGURATION INFORMATION 
FROM WEB.XML FILE.

7.HTTP SESSION:-SESSION TRACKING IS A WAY TO MAINTAIN A DATA OF AN USER.
->IT IS ALSO KNOWN AS SESSION MANAGEMENT.
->IN HTTP SESSION CONTAINER CREATES A SESSION ID FOR EACH USER.
THE CONTAINER USES THIS ID TO IDENTIFY THE PARTICULAR USER.
AN OBJECT OF HTTP SESSION IS USED TO TRACK THE SESSION OF A USER.
->FOR SESSION TRACKING WE HAVE SEVERAL OPTIONS:-
1.USER AUTHENTICATION
2.URL REWRITING
3.HTML HIDDEN FIELD
4.COOKIES
